        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 6:56PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vance, or 14 miles north of Centreville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Birmingham Fairgounds, Lipscomb, Shannon, Oak Mountain State Park,
Woodstock, Hoover Veterans Park, Green Pond, Pleasant Grove, Ensley,
Docena, Caffee Junction, Helena, Harmon, McCalla, Patton Creek,
Weller, McAdory, Hoover Metropolitan Stadium, Mercedes Benz Of
Alabama, and Lake View.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
